  'https://resources.isimangaliso.com/images/files/education/Application%20form_Tertiary%20Edu%20Support%202026.pdf',
  'https://www.zabursaries.co.za/science-bursaries-south-africa/isimangaliso-wetland-park-bursary/',
  ARRAY['mailto:nosipho@isimangaliso.com', 'https://resources.isimangaliso.com/images/files/education/Application%20form_Tertiary%20Edu%20Support%202026.pdf', 'mailto: nosipho@isimangaliso.com']::text[],
  NULL,
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must be a verifiable member of either: The Land Claimants Communities from iSimangaliso Wetland Park Authority (Sokhulu, Bhangazi, Dukuduku, Western Shores, Mdletsheni, Makhasa, Mnqobokazi, Nside, Ngwenya, Jobe, Mabaso, Emandleni, (Mbila) and Triangle (Mbila), and Coastal Reserves); OR be a resident of areas of Mkhanyakude District Municipality that are close to iSimangaliso Wetland Park or the Mfolozi Local Municipality particularly in the Sokhulu area You must intend on studying towards a qualification within the Conservation, Tourism or a related discipline You must entering your 1st year of study in 2026 You must be accepted to study at one the following institutions: University of KwaZulu-Natal, University of Zululand, Mangosuthu University of Technology and Durban University of Technology You must have applied for NSFAS bursary, or have confirmation that you have been awarded a NSFAS bursary You must have a passion for nature',
  'Download and complete the iSimangaliso Wetland Park Bursary Application Form 2026 (.pdf) Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the iSimangaliso Wetland Park Bursary. Submit clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your completed application form (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your may application be disqualified): ID document (certified copy) Proof of NSFAS bursary application Proof of registration or acceptance to UKZN, UniZulu, MUT or DUT Proof of residence If you are a member of a land claimant community: official letter from the Chairperson of the Board of Trustees of your land claim Trust confirming that you are a member of the land claim community If you are a member of iSimangaliso neighbouring communities: official letter from your local leader / councillor confirming that you are from the area and the length of time you have been living there Applications must be submitted via email to: nosipho@isimangaliso.com (Insert the words " iSimangaliso Bursary 2026 " in the email subject line).',
