  'https://nwsd.co.za/online-application/',
  'https://www.zabursaries.co.za/music-and-performing-arts-bursaries-south-africa/gert-johan-coetzee-bursary/',
  ARRAY['https://nwsd.co.za/online-application/']::text[],
  NULL,
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must be 18 years or older You must be currently in Matric or have completed Matric with a Diploma exemption or equivalent You must intend on studying full-time towards a 3 year Fashion Design course at the North West School of Design in Klerksdorp You must be able to start your studies in February 2026 You must be willing to commit to 3 years of study You must be fluent in English (read, write and speak) You must read the NWSD course prospectus (.pdf)',
  'Applicants must follow these steps to apply: Step 1: Complete the NWSD Course Application Step 2: Record a short video introducing yourself and answering: “If you could design an outfit for someone iconic, who would it be – and why?” The video should be no more than 1 minute 30 seconds long. The video should show your creativity, personality, and passion — this could be your breakthrough into the fashion industry! Step 3: Share your video on Social Media Upload your video to TikTok and Instagram Use the following hashtags: #nwsd #gert #gertbursary2025 #fashiondesign #fashionbursary #fashionschool Tag the following: @nwsdfashion and @gertjohancoetzee Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the Gert-Johan Coetzee Bursary.',
  'Arts',
  ARRAY['All']::text[],
  ARRAY[]::text[],
  FALSE,
  TRUE,
  now()
),
