  ARRAY['mailto:Bursaries2018@wrseta.org.za', 'https://indicium.wrseta.org.za/WRSETAIndicium/Pages/OnlineRegistration/OnlineBursaryRegistration.aspx']::text[],
  'W&RSETA will be awarding 2000 bursaries to new unemployed TVET students and 1000 bursaries to new unemployed HET students. The bursary programme is open to students who are studying (or intend to study) within the Wholesale and Retail Sector Scarce Skills, particularly the following fields: HETI UNIVERSITY PROGRAMMES (Degrees/ Diplomas): Accounting Food Technology/ Nutrition Technology Financial Management Information Technology Computer Science Logistics Management Purchasing Management Retail Business Management Retail Marketing Sales and Marketing Management Supply Chain Management NATED PROGRAMMES TVET (N4 – N6): Business Management Clothing Production Financial Management Hospitality and Catering Services Human Resource Management Management Assistant Marketing Management NCV PROGRAMMES (LEVEL 2 - LEVEL 4): Accounting, Economics & Finance Hospitality Information Technology Computer Science Office Administration Marketing Transport and Logistics The following expenses will be covered by the bursary programme: tuition fees, prescribed books, meals and accommodation.',
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): South African citizen Have registered OR have been accepted to study at a recognised tertiary institution (University/ University of Technology/ TVET College) in South Africa Studying (or intend on studying) full-time in one of the aforementioned fields Do NOT have any other sources of funding for your studies',
  'University / University of Technology students: Apply online at: http://indicium.wrseta.org.za/WRSETAIndicium/Pages/OnlineRegistration/OnlineBursaryRegistration.aspx TVET College students: Download and complete the WRSETA TVET Bursary Application Form (word doc) Completed application forms (and supporting documentation) must be emailed to: Bursaries2018@wrseta.org.za Submit clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your completed application form (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your application be disregarded): ID document (certified copy) Matric Certificate/ Matric results/ NCV Level 4 Certificate (certified copy) Grade 9 final results for TVET College students (certified copy) Full academic record/ statement of results if available Proof of tertiary registration/ admission Proof of accommodation if applicable Parents/ guardians ID documents (certified copies) Parents/ guardians proof of income (employer’s details and latest payslips)',
  'Arts; General',
