  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must be between 17 and 35 years old You must have completed Matric with a minimum overall average of 65% You must be studying or intend on studying full-time towards a qualification in one of the fields listed above, in 2025 You must be studying or have been accepted / provisionally accepted to study at an accredited University in South Africa You must be passionate about pursuing a career in the Media industry You must have a total household income of less than R600 000 per annum Students with disabilities are encouraged to apply',
  'Applications must be submitted online at: eMedia Bursary Application 2025 Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the eMedia Bursary. Submit clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your online application (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your application may be disqualified): ID document (certified copy) Matric certificate Proof of acceptance from a South African university Breakdown of academic fees per annum Parents or guardians proof of household income (recent payslips or letters of employment if employed, and latest 3 months'' bank statements (not older than three months) for each parent or guardian) Details of any other private or public bursary funding received, if applicable: commitment letter stating the funding source and coverage amount',
