(
  'Film School Africa (FSA) Bursary South Africa 2022 - 2023',
  'FILM SCHOOL AFRICA (FSA)',
  'The programme is awarded to 4 to 6 candidates each year and the bursary ''s monetary value is based on the candidate''s financial needs. Both sacrifice and effort will be required from the candidate. Third year students may be offered an internship at studios and production comp...',
  NULL,
  0,
  '2022-09-14',
  'https://www.filmschoolafrica.org/applications/bursary-application',
  'https://www.zabursaries.co.za/universities/film-school-africa-fsa-bursary/',
  ARRAY['mailto:applications@filmschoolafrica.org', 'https://www.filmschoolafrica.org/applications/bursary-application', 'https://www.filmschoolafrica.org/forms/online-application-form']::text[],
  'The programme is awarded to 4 to 6 candidates each year and the bursary ''s monetary value is based on the candidate''s financial needs. Both sacrifice and effort will be required from the candidate. Third year students may be offered an internship at studios and production companies located near the college. www.zabursaries.co.za is committed to keeping you up to date with the latest bursary opportunities, and this article covers all details about the Film School Africa College Bursary.',
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must intend on studying at FSA College in Somerset West (Cape Town) You must be interested in pursuing studies in any of the above mentioned streams You must be willing to live on campus for 2 to 3 years, until you have completed your studies You must be willing to contribute in any way, based on your ability You must be able to prove financial need You must be Christian and be willing to work out your faith daily (including attending chapel services and devotions)',
  'Candidates must follow these steps to apply: Step 1: complete the FSA College Bursary Application Form Answer these 3 essay questions on the application form (after giving them a lot of thought and attention): Why should you be selected to receive the bursary? Give details about a challenging time or experience and how you overcame it. Give details about where you currently live, and details about your own and your parents or guardians financial situation. Note: please ensure that you give as much information as possible as this will strongly influence your application. Questions should preferably be answered in a word document and emailed to: applications@filmschoolafrica.org Attach clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your online application: 3 months of your latest bank statements 3 months of your parents or guardians latest bank statements Step 2: complete the FSA College Application for Film Studies Candidates will receive an email with further instructions after they have completed the 2 steps above.',
  'Arts',
  ARRAY['All']::text[],
  ARRAY['Production (Cinematography, Lighting, Sound recording)', 'Post-production (Editing, Sound Editing/ Design)']::text[],
  FALSE,
  TRUE,
  now()
),
(
