  ARRAY['https://www.zabursaries.co.za/general-bursaries-south-africa/barloworld-bursary-south-africa/']::text[],
  'The Barloworld Education Trust initiated the bursary scheme to help students fund their tertiary studies, in fields related to the core business of Barloworld - Engineering, IT and Sales/ Marketing. Bursaries are awarded within the following fields of study: IT/ Computer Sciences (BSc) Industrial Engineering (BEng/ BSc) Mechanical Engineering (BEng/ BSc) Mining Engineering (BEng/ BSc) Marketing Sales The bursary award will cover the following expenses: registration fees, examination fees, tuition, prescribed textbooks. Accommodation costs may also be covered in certain circumstances.',
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): South African citizen Black student (Coloured, Indian, Chinese or African) Completed Matric Studying full-time within one of the aforementioned fields of study Studying at a recognised University or University of Technology in South Africa Passed all your mid year exams (in the current year of study) From a previously disadvantaged background',
  'Students who meet the above minimum eligibility requirements can apply by submitting clear copies of the following supporting documentation (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your application be disregarded): ID document (certified copy) Matric certificate (certified copy) Full academic record/ transcript (on tertiary institution letterhead) Curriculum Vitae Motivational letter explaining why you deserve to be awarded a bursary Applications must be submitted to: The Barloworld Education Trust PO Box 782248 Sandton 2146',
