  NULL,
  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must be currently in Matric or have completed Matric/ NCV You must have completed the following subjects in Matric: Mathematics and Physical Science (for Agricultural Engineering or Bio-Resource Engineering students) OR Life Science, Physical Science and Mathematics (for Veterinary Technology students) You must be studying or intend on studying towards a qualification within one of the fields of study listed above You must be studying or intend on studying at a registered Higher Education Institution in South Africa You must be unemployed You must be in financial need, with a total household income of NOT more than R350 000 or NOT more than R600 000 if living with a disability Preference will be given to youth residing in the Eastern Cape, who are unemployed and from historically disadvantaged groups (however, students from outside of the Eastern Cape province may also apply)',
  'Download and complete the EC Department of Agriculture Bursary Application Form 2026 (.pdf) Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the EC Department of Agriculture Bursary. Submit the following supporting documentation along with your completed application form (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your application may be disqualified): ID document (certified copy) Matric/ NCV latest results, if currently in Matric Matric/ NCV certificate, if completed Matric (certified copy) Full academic record, if currently studying Proof of admission/ provisional admission/ proof of registration from a registered Higher Education Institution Proof of residence from a local municipality (less than 3 months old) Parents or guardians proof of combined annual household income (latest payslips if employed/ affidavit if unemployed/ proof of social grant if applicable) Parents or guardians ID documents Proof of any other bursary or sponsorship by another organisation, if applicable Youth with disabilities are encouraged to apply Students who meet the above criteria, may apply via email to: bursary@ecagriculture.gov.za (Insert the words "DOA Bursary 2026" in the email subject line). Note: applications submitted via fax or hand delivery will NOT be accepted.',
