  'The bursary will cover the following expenses: registration fees, tuition fees, exam fees, prescribed textbooks, meals and accommodation. Once students have graduated from their studies, they will be required to work within the Eastern Cape Health sector and aim to give back to the community. Shortlisted candidates will be contacted - if you have not received any feedback by 15 February 2019, you can regard your application as unsuccessful.',
