  'Applicants must satisfy the following minimum entry criteria before applying (please note that failure to satisfy all the requirements will lead to your application not being considered): You must be a South African citizen You must NOT be older than 28 years old on 31 December 2024 You must reside within the Mpumalanga province You must have completed Matric You must have passed a minimum of 7 subjects in Matric You must have achieved a minimum of level 4, for the following compulsory subjects in Matric: Mathematics, Physical Science, Life Sciences (Biology) and English You must meet the criteria to study at a tertiary institution You must be interested in studying towards a Medicine qualification in Cuba, in 2024 You must preferably be from a disadvantaged background Note: candidates can apply while waiting for their passport to be issued.',
