  'Applications must be submitted online at: NAC International Bursary Application 2025 Enter “www.zabursaries.co.za” in the field asking how you heard about the NAC South Africa International Bursary. Submit clear copies of the following supporting documentation along with your online application (the submission of these documents is compulsory – if any items are missing, your application may be disqualified): ID document (certified copy - not be older than 12 months) Curriculum Vitae Course structure/ content Study fees structure from tertiary institution Proof of acceptance/ registration at an accredited institution (on institutions letterhead) Transcript of results/ recognition of prior learning qualification by academic institutions Certified copies of degrees/ certificates/ diplomas Proof of any other bursary funding (if applicable) Two reference letters from industry professionals (signed, dated with a full address and not be older than 12 months) (read our tips on how to get a letter of reference/ testimonial for your bursary application ) Motivational letter stating why you should be awarded the bursary and your future career aspirations (read our tips on how to write a motivational letter for your bursary application ) Proof of household/ own income Bank statement/ proof of bank account (with a bank stamp not older than 6 months)',
